    {{ docs.heading('h2', 'Centered columns') }}

    <p>Depending on the data you need to display you may wish to center-align the content within a column. Use the <code>.u-text-align-center</code> class on both the <code>&lt;th&gt;</code> and <code>&lt;td&gt;</code> elements you wish to center.</p>

    <p>The ‘Live’ and ‘Visible’ columns on this page use this method.</p>

    {{ docs.heading('h2', 'Increased contrast') }}

    <p>Some patterns, such as the form table pattern, place tables on a darker background. The <code>.table--contrast</code> class will use a darker background on the table body.</p>

    {{ docs.example({
        html: "<table class=\"table table--full table--contrast\">" ~ tableBody ~ "</table>"
    }) }}

